node.title: Oil supply is expected to catch up to demand, offering relief on prices.
node.description: The International Energy Agency said that the key factor in its improved outlook was rising production in the United States, Canada and Brazil.

node.title: Two-week quarantine rules for arrivals from southern Africa to end on Wednesday
node.description: NSW Health says scrapping the rules previously impacting arrivals from eight countries of concern will bring all international travellers under the same requirements.

node.title: Auto exec hired hitmen to kill mistress and blackmailer, feds say
node.description: Erik Charles Maund allegedly paid $750,000 to two ex-Marines and a former Israeli soldier to kidnap and kill his former mistress and her boyfriend.

node.title: The latest COVID-linked shortage? Salvation Army bell ringers
node.description: The organization says the shortfall is leaving 20,000 hours unfilled.

node.title: Confront the Obvious: The Jets and Giants Are Bad
node.description: Without three top playmakers, quarterback Zach Wilson had few good options against the Saints. The Giants yielded a three-touchdown day to the Chargers’ Justin Herbert.

node.title: New York stopped taking applications for pandemic rent aid. Now it faces a lawsuit.
node.description: Tenant and housing groups are seeking to force the state to start accepting applications for pandemic rent relief again, arguing that closing the program left many struggling renters vulnerable to eviction.
